# Your context

Copy this file to `INTERESTS.md` in the same folder, then edit. Everything below is a template — keep what's useful, rewrite or delete what's not. This file is gitignored, so it stays local to your clone.

## Professional background

- **Primary languages / frameworks:** (e.g., Python + Flask, TypeScript + React, Go, Rust, Swift)
- **Shipped products:** (list a few — what you built, who it was for, what you learned)
- **Current role:** (your day job, contract work, consulting, etc.)
- **Domain expertise:** (industries, regulatory contexts, technical specialties — anywhere you have inside-track knowledge)

## Interests / hobbies

- (Things you'd consider building a product around — even if unrelated to your day job)
- (Sports, hobbies, communities you're part of)
- (Topics you read about for fun)

## Industries with inside-track knowledge

- (Where you understand the workflows, pain points, jargon, and unwritten rules better than an outsider would)
- (This is high-value for founder-fit discovery — products in these spaces have a built-in unfair advantage)

## Product ideas I've already had

- (Things you've thought about building but haven't acted on yet — `/discover` can mine these as inputs)
- (Even half-formed ideas; just capture them)

## Things I do NOT want to work on

- (Categories that don't interest you, even if commercially viable — useful as a negative filter)
- (E.g., "not gambling," "not adtech," "not anything regulated by FDA")

## Risk profile

- **Solo budget for a build:** (hours/week + months you'd commit before validating)
- **Tolerance for a stretch stack:** (would you learn a new framework for the right product, or stay in known territory?)
- **Revenue vs. scale preference:** (lifestyle/profitable indie business vs. VC-track growth play)

## Anything else worth seeding the discovery with

- (Capability shifts you've noticed and want to act on)
- (Communities you're part of where you've seen recurring complaints)
- (Adjacencies to your shipped work you've been curious about)
